1. INNER JOIN [ Dashboards & Reports]
- Returns only rows that match in both tables

Ex: Show only valid transactions (users who placed orders)
𝖲𝖤𝖫𝖤𝖢𝖳 𝗎.𝗎𝗌𝖾𝗋_𝗂𝖽, 𝗎.𝗇𝖺𝗆𝖾, 𝗈.𝗈𝗋𝖽𝖾𝗋_𝗂𝖽, 𝗈.𝖺𝗆𝗈𝗎𝗇𝗍
𝖥𝖱𝖮𝖬 𝗎𝗌𝖾𝗋𝗌 as 𝗎
𝖨𝖭𝖭𝖤𝖱 𝖩𝖮𝖨𝖭 𝗈𝗋𝖽𝖾𝗋𝗌 𝗈
𝖮𝖭 𝗎.𝗎𝗌𝖾𝗋_𝗂𝖽 = 𝗈.𝗎𝗌𝖾𝗋_𝗂𝖽;

SELECT u.user_id, u.name, o.order_id, o.amount
FROM users u
JOIN orders o ON u.user_id = o.user_id;
-- Show me users who actually ordered something

2. LEFT JOIN (All Left + Matching Right) - Find Missing Data – Super Important in Industry
Returns all rows from left table and matching rows from right table
If no match in right-> right columns = NULL

𝗦𝗘𝗟𝗘𝗖𝗧 𝘂.𝘂𝘀𝗲𝗿_𝗶𝗱, 𝘂.𝗻𝗮𝗺𝗲, 𝗼.𝗼𝗿𝗱𝗲𝗿_𝗶𝗱
𝗙𝗥𝗢𝗠 𝘂𝘀𝗲𝗿𝘀 𝘂
𝗟𝗘𝗙𝗧 𝗝𝗢𝗜𝗡 𝗼𝗿𝗱𝗲𝗿𝘀 𝗼
𝗢𝗡 𝘂.𝘂𝘀𝗲𝗿_𝗶𝗱 = 𝗼.𝘂𝘀𝗲𝗿_𝗶𝗱;

Ex: Find users who never placed an order (activation metric)
SELECT u.user_id, u.name
FROM users u
LEFT JOIN orders o ON u.user_id = o.user_id
WHERE o.order_id IS NULL;
 -- Show me users even if they have no orders

