4. FULL OUTER JOIN (MySQL Workaround) - Audit & Reconciliation kosam
-> Returns rows that exist in either table (matched + unmatched both sides)

Ex: Find mismatches between systems (e.g., orders vs payments)
SELECT u.user_id, u.name, o.order_id
FROM users u
LEFT JOIN orders o ON u.user_id = o.user_id
UNION
SELECT u.user_id, u.name, o.order_id
FROM users u
RIGHT JOIN orders o ON u.user_id = o.user_id;
-- It's like show everything, matched or not

5. SELF JOIN (Table Joined With Itself) - Hierarchies & Referrals
-> Joins a table to itself using aliases

Ex: Employee–Manager mapping, referral chains
SELECT e.name AS employee, m.name AS manager
FROM employees e
LEFT JOIN employees m
  ON e.manager_id = m.emp_id;

6. CROSS JOIN (All Combinations anochu) - Matrices & Test Data
-> Returns every combination of rows from both tables

Ex: Pricing combinations, feature experiments
SELECT u.name, p.plan_name
FROM users u
CROSS JOIN plans p;
-- Remember SPARK this CROSS JOIN Can create huge result sets chuskoni vaadali

